[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Inhibiting a fully national recovery[bold] –
[normal] 
[normal]a sustainable recovery cannot be restricted to particular regions or any one of the four main industrial groupings. Counties account for more than half of all Gross Value Added (GVA) generat
[normal]ed outside of London. Effective fiscal devolution to county regions will allow CCN members to better support diversified growth across the UK; excluded areas may not have access to the necessary levers to kick start growth, particularly in low growth sub-r
[normal]egional areas that require high levels of support.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Disproportionate growth[bold] [bold]opportunities -[bold] Cities already enjoy greater effective freedoms, flexibilities, growth incentives and localised Whitehall budgets than their 
[normal]county
[normal] peers. Extending further powers 
[normal]and funding to cities while excluding counties from the process could exaggerate this situation to the extent of defining access to decision-making power by where a voter lives, ignoring local needs and growth potential.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Growing[bold] 
[normal]socio-economic inequalitie[bold]s[bold] – 
[normal]Fiscal devolution is an important way of tackling the 
[normal]socio-economic 
[normal]challenges created by fiscal austerity, including the impact on deprived communities and the demand-led pressures of a rapidly ageing population.
[normal] 
[normal]Extending further powers and funding 
[normal]to cities while excluding counties could exaggerate the socio-economic and demographic challenges facing counties.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Constraining county capacity to support growth by[bold] [bold]misaligning incentives and misplacing powers[bold] - [bold]Restricting access to growth related schemes creates striking discrepancies, including in the youth contract, business rate retention and Revolving Infrastructure Funds. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
